      <abstract>
        <p>Consumers and business in India bought 800,000 personal computers in October-to-November quarter of 2003, increase of 87 percent over year-earlier period (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Consumers and business in India bought 800,000 personal computers in the October-to-November quarter of 2003, an increase of 87 percent over the year-earlier period, the Manufacturers Association of Information Technology said yesterday. It said sales could total more than three million in the fiscal year ending in March.</p>
        <p>Saritha Rai (NYT)</p>
      </block>
